Services have been suspended between Bankstown and Birrong in that direction only due to a person injured by a train at Yagoona. Delays and service changes are occurring as a result.

T3 Lidcombe via Bankstown Line services will terminate and commence from Bankstown.

Bus services have been contacted to provide a replacement service between Bankstown and Lidcombe in both directions.

T3 Liverpool via Bankstown services travelling from the City will operate via the T2 Inner West & Leppington Line stopping Central, Redfern, Strathfield, Lidcombe, then all stations to Liverpool via Regents Park.

T3 Liverpool via Bankstown services travelling to the City will operate as normal.

Please allow additional travel time, listen to announcements, check station information screens and transport apps for individual service information.

Continue to allow plenty of additional travel time due to a train requiring mechanical repairs at Ingleburn.

Train crew are attempting to rectify the issue, however we have no forecast for completion of repairs and the resumption of services heading towards the City between Macarthur and Glenfield.

Services from Glenfield heading towards Macarthur may also experience delays and larger than normal gaps on services.

Buses are being arranged to provide a replacement service between Campbelltown and Glenfield and should start arriving on site at Ingleburn at 09:45hrs, at Minto at 10:00hrs and at Campbelltown at 10:00hrs

Please listen to announcements, check information screens for service updates as stopping patterns and departure platforms may change at short notice.

Delays to services up to 20 minutes due to heavy rain activating track safety monitors at Wondabyne.  Increased journey times and larger than normal service gaps may be experienced.

Please allow extra travel time, listen to announcements, check information screens and transport apps as some stopping patterns and departure platforms may change.

Hunter Line: Buses replace trains between Newcastle Interchange, Maitland and Scone/Dungog due to severe weather conditions causing flooding at Sandgate, Islington Junction and between Maitland and Scone/Dungog. 

Please  avoid any non-essential travel, make your own arrangements or if travelling - allow plenty of extra travel time.

There are 18 buses in operation between Newcastle interchange and Scone/Dungog

NRL: Warriors vs Knights Central Coast Stadium
18:00 to 20:00
- The closest station to Central Coast Stadium is Gosford.

A - League Sydney Wanderers vs Perth Glory 
19:00 to 21:00
- The closest station to Bankwest Stadium is Parramatta. The stadium is approximately 15 minutes walk from the station exiting via Darcy St then continuing on Church St, the Riverside Walk (non-accessible route) or through Prince Alfred Square to the stadium on O'Connell St.

For more information visit https://transportnsw.info/events/2021/03
Be weather wise and avoid rushing and stepping in puddles to prevent slips, trips and falls.

There are changes happening at Central Station due to Sydney Metro construction works. Access to certain areas of the station and platforms may mean using different stairs, escalators and lifts. Please follow the signs and staff directions. If you need assistance, see station staff. For detailed information please visit https://transportnsw.info/alerts/details#/6049959

From 11 January to end-December 2021, the escalators and staircase connecting the corner of Pitt Street and Eddy Avenue with the Grand Concourse and L1 Light Rail stop will be closed due to station upgrade works. 

To access the Grand Concourse and Platforms 1 to 12 from the street level, please use the Western Forecourt entry via Pitt Street. To access Platforms 16 to 25 from the street level, please use the Eddy Avenue entry. 

To access Pitt Street or Eddy Avenue from the Grand Concourse or L1 light rail stop, please exit the station via the Western Forecourt or Northern Concourse.
Due to station redevelopment work some platforms have reduced capacity. Please avoid standing in front of construction zones and remain behind the yellow line on the platform

Platforms 4, 5 & 6 upgrade works. A new Metro concourse is being constructed on the northern end of Sydenham Station. While the concourse is being installed, please board and alight from the first 5 carriages of the train on platforms 4 & 6 and the last 6 carriages of the train on platform 5. If you need help, please ask staff at the station. For more information on these upgrades, please see sydneymetro.info
